# Avandad — Layout Helper · V1.1
# =====================================================================
# Optional environment configuration. NOTHING in this file is required
# to boot the app for designer testing — the defaults point at the
# bundled sample plans and produce all runtime files (uploads,
# processed slab data, exports) into a data/ directory the app
# creates on demand.
#
# Copy this file to ``.env`` if your environment supports it, or set
# the variables in your shell before launching the backend.

# ---- Application data directory --------------------------------------
# Root under which uploads/, processed/ and exports/ subdirectories
# are created on first use. Absolute paths are used verbatim; relative
# paths are resolved against the shell's working directory.
# AVANDAD_DATA_DIR=./data

# ---- Slab inventory override ----------------------------------------
# Absolute path to a ``clean_slabs.json`` file that overrides the
# Step-3 upload flow. When unset the API waits for an upload — nothing
# on disk is silently used as a fallback. Legacy alias:
# STONELAYOUT_INVENTORY_PATH still works for operators upgrading from
# V1.0.0.
# AVANDAD_INVENTORY_PATH=/absolute/path/to/clean_slabs.json

# ---- ODA File Converter (DWG import) --------------------------------
# Only needed if you plan to import DWG plans. DXF works without it.
# ODA_FILE_CONVERTER_PATH=/Applications/ODAFileConverter.app/Contents/MacOS/ODAFileConverter
